# Facebook Live Stream Plugin

The Facebook Live Stream Plugin allows you to embed Facebook live streams on your WordPress website and collect feedback from your audience.

## Features

- Display Facebook live streams on your website.
- Collect feedback from viewers with a customizable feedback form.
- Display the live stream and feedback form together on any post, page, or widgetized area.

## Installation

1. Download the plugin zip file from the GitHub repository.
2. In your WordPress admin panel, navigate to Plugins > Add New.
3. Click on the "Upload Plugin" button, select the plugin zip file, and click "Install Now."
4. Activate the plugin.

## Usage

### Shortcode

Use the following shortcode to display the Facebook live stream and feedback form together on any post or page:

```
[facebook_live_stream_with_feedback]
```

### Widget

You can also use the Facebook Live Stream Widget to display the live stream and feedback form together in a widgetized area of your theme.

1. Go to Appearance > Widgets in your WordPress admin panel.
2. Drag the "Facebook Live Stream Widget" to the desired widget area.
3. Enter your Facebook Access Token and Page ID in the widget settings.

### Feedback Form and Live Stream Together

You can display the live stream and feedback form together by using the shortcode or widget in your posts, pages, or widgetized areas. This allows your audience to watch the live stream and submit feedback simultaneously, enhancing user engagement and interaction.

## Configuration

Before using the plugin, you'll need to obtain a Facebook Access Token and Page ID:

1. **Access Token**: Generate a Facebook Access Token from the Facebook Developer Console. Make sure the token has the `pages_show_list` and `pages_read_engagement` permissions.
2. **Page ID**: Obtain the ID of the Facebook page where the live stream will be broadcasted.

Once you have obtained the Access Token and Page ID, you can configure the plugin settings in the WordPress admin panel.

## Compatibility

This plugin is compatible with all modern WordPress themes. However, some themes or plugins may require additional styling adjustments for optimal display.

